  {
    "client_msg_id": "33ae8c24-feb6-4f31-a81c-bb070680943a",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Interesting. I know this question isn't about 'future of programming' but if we try and dig into why typical copy-paste isn't context aware, we might get to something useful. E.g. our current copy-paste produces a piece of text that is completely disconnected from its context. The reader is then expected to recreate the context. In a different kind of substrate, the copy-paste wouldn't server the link, a reader would just evaluate the code 'in-context' and make changes live to produce a new version.",
    "user": "U8A5MS6R1",
    "ts": "1533956540.000024",
